- OOC Respect<br>
Respect all members, regardless of their IC rank. Do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> fight OOC on the boards, any OOC fights should be taken care of over IM or email, or just simply avoided.<br>
- IC respect<br>
Respect is a major issue with felines. The dominant [higher ranking] cats deserve to be treated just as that - higher ranking cats. Respect can be shown by letting the higher ranking cats eat first, letting them walk ahead, etc.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Characters</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- Each player may have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>one</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> cat character. You may have two characters if you wish to play a forest creature as well as a cat, but you must seek permission from Harper before doing so.<br>
- Characters must be real cat colors. For a list of these go to General Cat Information. No pink footed, orange tailed, yellow bellied, purple eared kitties with poofy white wings! <br>
- If your character is below ten months, it is a kitten and will be given an apprentice rank!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mates and Kittens</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- Any cat is allowed to have a mate; if you find one, post in this forum announcing who you are mated to so we can fix your title. Being mated to someone does not mean like it does with canines. Being mates mean you love the other deeply, but breeding is not restricted to the one cat.<br>
- Do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> role play out the mating process.<br>
- Leaders may breed freely. Anyone else who wishes to breed must seek ooc permission from their leaders. You do not have to have a mate (as in an official one that would be place in your title) to have kittens.<br>
- Kittens may be played NPC for up to two months, then you need to have someone to play them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Time</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- We go in real time. two months OOC is two months IC. Sat grow at a normal speed, and they die.<br>
- Time during threads is different. If a thread is started on July 12th and the basic thread is: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>'It is morning, around 11:00 AM. Cat1 grooms himself, climbs a tree and sleeps.'</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> At the end of the post it is about 11:30, not much time has passed. The next person to reply takes three days. Their post is: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>'Cat2 finds the place where cat1 has groomed. Sniffs it, and looks up to see Cat1. She climbs up and taps Cat1 and says hi.'</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Though it took three days for someone to reply. Cat1 was not asleep for three days. it is now July 12th at 11:45 AM.<br>
<br>
